11/03/2010
LONDON, United Kingdom -- A London court released former Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) presidency member Ejup Ganic on bail Thursday (March 11th), pending extradition proceedings set for March 29th.
Serbia has sent an official extradition request, according to Justice Ministry official Slobodan Homen.
Ganic was arrested on March 1st at London's Heathrow Airport based on a warrant issued by Belgrade.
Serbia wants him in connection with a May 1992 attack in Sarajevo against a Yugoslav National Army convoy, which left more than 40 soldiers dead.
(BBC, AFP, DPA, AP - 11/03/10;
Beta, Tanjug, RTS, B92 - 10/03/10)
